High Speed Rail Solutions understands the criticality of safe integration in railway projects and know the risks that can quickly emerge when engineering changes are being made to functioning railway infrastructure.

We work with Infrastructure Managers, Local Authorities, Equipment Manufacturers, Design, Construction and other professional services organisations to successfully integrate complex railway systems and demonstrate that they are safe, reliable and compliant.

We prevent the following risks from occurring:
> Delays to Commissioning and Authorisation for Placing into Service;
> Increased cost to complete;
> Reputational damage;
> Improvement / Enforcement Notices;
> Prosecution;
> Loss of Life.

Our specialist Systems Engineering and Assurance services keep those that interact with the railway system free from harm, keep people moving and demonstrate how legal requirements are being met. These services include:
> System Safety Engineering (CSM-RA compliance)
> Conformance to Railway Regulatory Law (e.g. National Technical Specification Notices)
> Systems Engineering and Integration (e.g. Requirements and Interface Management)
> Reliability, Availability and Maintainability analysis;
> Independent Professional Reviews;
> Technical and Engineering Assurance.

We have been verified by the Railway Industry Supplier Qualification Scheme (RISQS) for a number of specialist RICCL Product Codes; Supplier ID 6413.

The Regulation (EU) 913/2010 concerning a European rail network for competitive freight, later amended by Regulation (EU) 1316/2013, required Member States together with European Infrastructure Managers to establish international market-oriented RFCs to meet three main challenges:
1) Strengthening cooperation between Infrastructure Managers (IMs) and Allocation Bodies (ABs).
2) Finding the right balance between freight and passenger traﬃc along RFCs.
3) Promoting intermodality between rail and other transport modes by integrating terminals into the corridor management process.

The EU’s trans-European transport (TEN-T) network policy, based on Regulation (EU) 1679/2024, is a key instrument for planning and developing a coherent, efficient, multimodal, and high-quality transport infrastructure across the EU. As part of the TEN-T governance, nine European Transport Corridors (ETCs) support the completion of the trans-European transport network, namely: 
(a) Atlantic;
(b) Baltic Sea-Black Sea-Aegean Sea*;
(c) Baltic Sea-Adriatic Sea;
(d) Mediterranean;
(e) North Sea-Rhine-Mediterranean;
(f) North Sea-Baltic;
(g) Rhine-Danube;
(h) Scandinavian-Mediterranean;
(i) Western Balkans-Eastern Mediterranean.

The European Transport Corridors integrate the Rail Freight Corridors (RFCs), that is, the freight railway lines of the ETCs. 

Since traﬃc does not usually start and end on one RFC exclusively, eﬃcient and synchronised interfaces to the existing processes and tools of individual IMs/ABs participating in RFCs are needed. An interactive tool developed jointly by RailNetEurope (RNE) and the RFCs is the Customer Information Platform (CIP). By means of a Graphical User Interface (GUI), CIP provides precise information on the routing, terminals, specific track properties and infrastructure investment projects, as well as International Contingency Management (ICM) and re-routing options of the participating Rail Freight Corridors (RFCs). More info on: https://cip.rne.eu/

L'équipe Marketing et Communication de la Direction Distribution TGV Europe vous propose de rester connectés à toute l'actualité et aux temps forts de l'univers Agences de Voyages et de SNCF Voyageurs. Cela, en collaboration avec les équipes commerciales qui vous accompagnent tout au long de l'année. 

Nous vous parlerons notamment des sujets suivants : 
- Les événements tout au long de l'année; 
- Les temps forts SNCF Voyageurs; 
- Et tous les sujets qui vous seront utiles. 

De plus, le site FERIA vous permet de rester connectés à l'actualité SNCF Voyageurs en vous informant et vous formant l'ensemble de l'offre SNCF Voyageurs.

The First Rail team is one of the most experienced in the industry; we run every type of train service – long distance, regional, commuter and sleeper services. We have three franchises – Avanti West Coast (AWC), South Western Railway (SWR) and Great Western Railway (GWR) plus our open access passenger services, Hull Trains and Lumo. We also operate Tramlink in Croydon on behalf of Transport for London and Heathrow Express with Heathrow Airport.

In addition to our Train Operating Companies (TOCs), First Rail includes: 

First Rail Holdings – a number of specialist teams such as Finance, Property, Engineering, Operations, IT, Procurement and Human Resources, all of which provide expertise and support to the rail division;

First Customer Contact Centre (FCC) in Sheffield, delivering a huge range of support services for our passengers, from handling group bookings, ticket sales and requests for travel assistance to managing complaints and customer compensation claims; 

First Rail Consultancy – providing specialist services across the public transport sector, particularly in the rail industry, ranging from commercial, customer experience, human resources, marketing, and programme and project management to bid writing, analysis, engineering, operations, and performance and planning;

evo-rail – supplying data connectivity solutions for the international rail market; and

Mistral Data – supplying innovative data analytic systems for the rail market.

Unicom Tranzit is one of the top 3 private rail freight carriers and forwarders operating in Romania since 1994. We are part of the Unicom Group.

The company’s philosophy is based on the following principles:
• our clients are treated as partners and we are aware that our success depends on their success;
• we try to attract and train people who want to excel and are able to capitalize on our material resources and to value especially themselves;
• we maintain a fleet of performant and diversified rolling stock, capable of efficiently meeting the requirements of rail transport.

As mentioned before, one of the strengths of our company is the competence of our team. This is made up of positive, intelligent people, keen to continuously improve the way we work and find the best solutions for our clients. Their training allows us to offer superior quality services that we strive to improve on a permanent basis.

We want to distinguish ourselves through the consistency with which we fulfill our commitments to our customers. We act on the principle that every customer is entitled to have the following expectations from us:
• to carry out in a timely and safe manner the engaged services;
• to maintain a relationship based on trust and transparency, fully informing the customer about any problem that has arisen and promptly acting to solve it;
• to learn from and adapt to our customer's requirements in order to help our customer optimize his business and logistics processes;
• to efficiently manage our resources and support our customer in his effort to be as competitive as possible on the market.

The rail transport system can be viewed as a vascular system of the modern economy. Its role is to bring the necessary resources to the right place at the right time. In this system, our company represents several arteries that, when we fulfill our mission, the parts that depend on us (our customers and partners) grow, develop and thus we thrive together.

