GRAMPET Group is the largest private rail freight and logistics holding in Romania and South Eastern Europe, offering solutions for customers’ complex businesses in the railway sector. 
For 20 years, we have been developing together the first multinational with Romanian capital, a leader in rail freight transport in Europe.

GRAMPET Group can supply integrated logistics services and freight transport solutions throughout the route that connects the Black Sea with the Adriatic Sea and the North Sea. 

Together with our partners, we have managed to become the largest group of private railway companies in South-Eastern Europe.
Here are the companies we are proud to have with us in this courageous endeavor and the different areas of activity that, through them, we can cover.

RAILWAY TRANSPORT COMPANIES: ROMANIAN RAILWAY GROUP, BULGARIAN RAILWAY COMPANY, TRAIN HUNGARY, EURORAIL LOGISTICS SERBIA, GRAMPET CARGO AUSTRIA GMBH, TEF RAILWAY LOGISTICS;

LOGISTICS SERVICES COMPANIES: ROLLING STOCK COMPANY, EURORAIL LOGISTICS GERMANY, EURORAIL COMPANY MOLDOVA, EURORAIL UKRAINE, GFR LOGISTIC BRAZI;

ROLLING STOCK DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION AND REPAIR COMPANIES: VFU PAȘCANI ELECTROPUTERS; REVA S.A. SIMERIA, RELOC S.A., GRAMPET DEBRECENI VAGONGYAR KFT .;

IT SOLUTIONS: INSTITUTE OF COMPUTER TECHNIQUE.

Rail Capital Partners Sp. z o. o. jest spółką typu „ROSCO” tzn. spółką posiadającą lokomotywy i dzierżawiącą je przewoźnikom kolejowym. Spółka została powołana do życia w 2012 roku w celu dzierżawienia klientom nowoczesnych lokomotyw. Właścicielem Spółki jest Fundusz Inwestycyjny FIZ AN („Fundusz”), którego częścią portfela inwestycyjnego zarządza Polski Fundusz Rozwoju S.A. Główna działalność biznesowa Spółki skupiona jest organizacyjnie w następujących segmentach:
• Dzierżawa / leasing pojazdów trakcyjnych;
• Utrzymanie pojazdów trakcyjnych.

Clerconnect Sàrl propose principalement les services suivants :
- Conseils et expertises techniques : Accompagnement pour répondre aux enjeux spécifiques de vos projets;
- Études : Analyses approfondies pour garantir la fiabilité et la performance des installations;
- Coordination de projets : Gestion technique et coordination pour assurer la réussite de vos projets;
- Exécution de projets : suivi de travaux, organisation de mises en services et de campagnes de tests.

Avec une approche centrée sur la proximité et la compréhension des besoins de mes clients, je m'efforce de fournir des solutions sur mesure et de qualité, adaptées aux défis techniques complexes de chaque projet.

Particulièrement intéressé par les nouvelles technologies, notamment le CBTC (Contrôle de Trains Basé sur la Communication) et le FRMCS (Future Railway Mobile Communication System), pour offrir des solutions innovantes et à la pointe du progrès, je me réjouis de collaborer avec des partenaires et des compagnies dans ces domaines passionnants et en constante évolution. N'hésitez pas à me contacter pour toute information ou pour une rencontre !

We are an Engineer and Commercial Representation Company

Somos uma empresa de Engenharia e de Representação Comercial   

A FASSER fornece produtos e serviços de engenharia na área ferroviária e metroviária, atendendo as operadoras de transporte de passageiro e carga. 

Efetuamos o projeto, a implantação, o comissionamento, e a manutenção de sistemas de eletrificação, sinalização, telecomunicação e ventilação. 

Oferecemos produtos para metrôs, ferrovias e monotrilhos:
 - Sistemas completos de trilho condutor / terceiro trilho;
 - Pantógrafos e sapatas coletoras;
 - Equipamentos de sinalização como maquinas de chave e sinaleiros;
 - Sistemas de transmissão de dados;
 - Atenuadores de ruídos para sistemas de ventilação primária.

Kimberley Systems Engineering Limited (KSEL) (www.KSEL.org.uk) provides systems engineering services in a broad range of industries with detailed practical knowledge in System Engineering, System Safety & Risk Assessment, Safety Engineering and Management in the development of high integrity safety systems, RAM, Human Factors and Verification and Validation related activities. KSEL has a working knowledge of the regulations, standards and principles to be applied in these areas together with many years of application experience across a range of projects, clients, industries and countries. KSEL, working in liaison with the client, deliver professional and bespoke risk centered solutions recognising the complexity, criticality and constraints of the system and related domain,

KSEL services include:
•	Systems Engineering;
•	System Safety Management;
•	Safety Case production and Management;
•	Hazard Identification (HAZID, HAZOP);
•	Hazard Analysis (FMECA/FMEA);
•	Independent Safety Assessment;
•	Reliability Improvement (including FRACAS and DRACAS);
•	RAM assessments;
•	Risk Analysis (Qualitative and Quantitative QRA);
•	Risk Modelling (statistical, predictive, stochastic);
•	Fault and Event Tree Analysis;
•	ALARP and Cost Benefit Analysis;
•	Operations Safety Hazard Analysis (OSHA).

About us
After over twenty years of individual experience in Systems Engineering in a wide variety of engineering disciplines with focus on Systems Engineering and System Safety Engineering, Jonathan Harding (Harding Consultancy) and Mukesh Sharma (QSD Critical Systems) have decided to create a joint enterprise in the name of Kimberley Systems Engineering Limited. With their own knowledge of Systems Engineering and practical experience in various industries and with their network of employees and associates gives them the capability to offer the appropriate level of tailored Systems Engineering solutions for their clients.

